<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis box="[198,330,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Comments.</emphasis>
Member of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[618,755,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Solomonius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[618,755,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Solomonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are relatively large for the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[1091,1227,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Solomonius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1091,1227,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Solomonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. The male genitalia are distinctive in possessing elongate, robust, dorsolateral lobes. This is the only genus in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,288,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Solomonius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Solomonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group in which the medial penile plates of the aedeagus are elongate and protrude outside of the genital capsule. Species in this genus can be distinguished from one another with the following key.
</paragraph>
